Privacy Policy
Privacy Overview
This is a snapshot of how 1 Second Everyday, P.B.C. treats personal information and data with the 1SE app.
Limited collection of your data
Our default position is to collect as little information as possible. We may collect and keep data about you, like your email address, location, and individual snippets only when you allow us to. We also collect non-personal data like de-identified and/or aggregated information data with our analytical partners (like Apple, Flurry, and Firebase). This is to help us build a better 1SE and provide the best experience to you. Our privacy policy has a whole section on what we collect and why, in a user friendly table. You can
view the table here
.
It's your data
If you would like to download, change, or delete your data please take a look at our step-by-step guides for
How to download your data
,
How to change your data
, and
How to delete your data
. You can also opt-out of certain uses and disclosure of your Personal Information, as described in Section 5 of our Privacy Policy.
Retain data only for as long as necessary
We don't want to hold onto personal data any longer than is needed. To help prevent this, we have a data retention schedule for various types of data we collect. This is primarily for when someone doesn't use 1SE for longer than a year. Of course, we'll make multiple attempts to notify the user before any action is taken. Our privacy policy has a friendly table that shows our data retention schedule and you can
view it here
.
Best practices for security
We take multiple steps to ensure your data is secure. First, we regularly perform security audits on our key systems. Next, access to critical systems are limited to only a few team members. Lastly, 1SE data is encrypted in transit and at rest. We'll also make sure that the other businesses we work with protect your data.
Privacy FAQ
No matter where you're located, 1 Second Everyday, P.B.C. believes in your Privacy.
Who has access to my videos, journal, and other personal data?
No one will ever access your backed up files without permission or unless required by law. Our support or engineering team will only view your data if you give us explicit permission to, for example, help in a technical support situation.
Do you monetize how I use 1SE, my videos, or any of my personal data?
Nope.
Do you listen to my videos, record without me knowing, or other creepy things without my permission?
No
Are you going to share my 1SE videos on social media?
No. You own your videos. We only share someone's 1SE video if they give us permission to do so, like for a hashtag challenge or if they have shared publicly on their social media channels. We will always ask and receive permission before sharing on our own social media channels.
Where is my data stored?
1SE uses Amazon Web Services (AWS) servers. These data centers are exclusively within the US right now.
How secure is my data on 1SE?
We use the same security and encryption standards as government agencies and Fortune 100 companies and limit team access to our systems using CIS20 guidelines.
Is my data encrypted?
Yes. In transit end to end using SSL and while at rest at using 256-bit AES.
Will my account be deleted after a period of inactivity?
If your account is inactive for 18 months, we will delete your account and all data associated with it. Multiple notifications will be sent to the account holder before this happens though. This is a part of our data retention policy found in our
privacy policy here
.
What can I do to take control of personalized advertisements I receive on other platforms?
You may opt-out of personalized advertisements by following the instructions for
Android
and
iOS
. You can also learn more about targeted advertising and consumer choice and privacy, at
www.networkadvertising.org/managing/opt_out.asp
, or
http://www.youronlinechoices.eu/
and
www.aboutads.info/choices/
.
If you have any questions about our privacy practices, please contact us by email at
privacy@1secondeveryday.com
. We will address your concerns and attempt to resolve any privacy issues in a timely manner.
1 Second Everyday, P.B.C.
Privacy Policy
Effective Date of Current Policy: 11/14/23
Introduction
Welcome to 1 Second Everyday's privacy policy.
1 Second Everyday respects your privacy and is committed to protecting your personal data. This privacy policy will inform you as to how we look after your personal data when you visit our website (regardless of where you visit it from) and use our services and tell you about your privacy rights and how the law protects you.
This privacy policy is provided in a layered format so you can click through to the specific areas set out below. Alternatively, you can download the policy here:
1 Second Everyday Privacy Policies
. Please also use the Glossary to understand the meaning of some of the terms used in this privacy policy.
Other relevant policies are our
Cookie Policy
,
Terms of Service
, and
CCPA Policy
.
